From 5b60ea953e3458ca16064fe3f1266e52646dd4b8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Slick <slick@slicksync.local>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 05:40:43 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: chain-link logo, now theme-reactive

Replaced the v1.9.13 gradient spark mark (which clashed against the
sidebar badge's own theme-colored gradient background) with a
chain-link icon, built as an inline SVG component (SlickSyncLogo)
rather than a static PNG. The badge container already uses
--color-primary/--color-secondary per active theme; the mark itself
is a flat white stroke, checked for contrast against all 8 themes'
palettes (all use solid, saturated colors - no low-contrast risk on
any of them).

Replaced every static <img src="/logo-white.png"> usage: Sidebar,
UserSidebar, InviteLayout, CreateUserModal (both the create and
reconnect steps, which also removed the now-dead isDark/logoSrc
light-dark-file-switching logic), and the login page.

Favicon/apple-touch-icon stay static PNGs (browser tab icons can't
respond to in-app theme state) using the same chain-link mark on the
brand's Slick violet-cyan gradient.

Bump to 1.9.14, changelog entry added.
